</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BE20F2E331FFDFFF6DFC93939CFBD1" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="101B7379E331FFDFFF6DFC9391ECFCD1" blockId="26.[192,896,866,954]" box="[192,896,866,890]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFF6DFC939342FCD1" bold="true" box="[192,302,866,890]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Ecology</emphasis>
. Lowland. Habitat unknown; probably riparian.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E331FFDFFF6DFC509029FC11" blockId="26.[192,896,866,954]" box="[192,581,929,954]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFF6DFC509345FC12" bold="true" box="[192,297,929,953]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: January.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E331FFDFFF6DFC1093F7FBB1" blockId="26.[192,1440,993,1146]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFF6DFC1093CCFC51" bold="true" box="[192,416,993,1018]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Macropterous, probably capable of flight. Moderate runner. Vagility likely favoured by flight capacity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E331FFDFFF6DFBB0939CFBD1" blockId="26.[192,1440,993,1146]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFF6DFBB09320FBF2" bold="true" box="[192,332,1089,1113]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Reference</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="74350E88E331FFDFFEF4FBB3909EFBF2" author="Larochelle, A. &amp; M. - C. Lariviere" box="[345,754,1089,1114]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 281" refId="ref33655" refString="Larochelle, A., and M. - C. Lariviere. 2001. Carabidae (Insecta: Coleoptera): catalogue. Fauna of New Zealand 43: 1 - 281." type="journal article" year="2001">Larochelle and Larivière 2001: 85</bibRefCitation>
(catalogue; biology, dispersal power, ecology, geographic distribution, references).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BE20F2E331FFDFFF6DFB539757FA32" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="101B7379E331FFDFFF6DFB539757FA32" blockId="26.[192,1440,1186,1434]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFF6DFB539350FB11" bold="true" box="[192,316,1186,1210]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
. The authors have made abundant collections of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFC3EFB53961AFB11" box="[915,1142,1186,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFC3EFB539674FB11" box="[915,1048,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Bembidion</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in Teal Valley (NN) and neighbouring areas but could not secure new specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFC3DFB339643FB71" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[912,1071,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="townsendi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFC3DFB339643FB71" box="[912,1071,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. townsendi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is only known from the female 
<typeStatus id="CF1FCDDBE331FFDFFEB4FB1393EAFB51" box="[281,390,1250,1274]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
. In Teal Valley, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFDE7FB13919AFB52" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[586,1014,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviceps" subGenus="Zemetallina">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFDE7FB1390A3FB51" box="[586,719,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Bembidion</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFD72FB13911FFB51" box="[735,883,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Zemetallina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFC2FFB13919AFB52" box="[898,1014,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">parviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFB9CFB13971AFB52" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[1073,1398,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tairuense" subGenus="Zeplataphus">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFB9CFB139620FB52" box="[1073,1100,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFBF6FB139699FB51" box="[1115,1269,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Zeplataphus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFAA9FB13971AFB52" box="[1284,1398,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">tairuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– a rather small species morphologically close to and belonging to the same subgenus as 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFB1DFAF39720FAB1" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[1200,1356,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="townsendi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFB1DFAF39720FAB1" box="[1200,1356,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. townsendi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– were both abundant in the field. Two aberrant specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFCFCFAD396FCFA92" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[849,1168,1314,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviceps" subGenus="Zemetallina">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFCFCFAD39100FA92" box="[849,876,1314,1337]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFCD7FAD39662FA91" box="[890,1038,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Zemetallina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFBB1FAD396FCFA92" box="[1052,1168,1314,1337]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">parviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found; they were small in size like 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFE35FAB3905BFAF1" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[408,567,1346,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="townsendi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFE35FAB3905BFAF1" box="[408,567,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. townsendi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and possessed the 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFC89FAB391D2FAF1" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[804,958,1346,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Zeplataphus">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFC89FAB391D2FAF1" box="[804,958,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Zeplataphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
character of the elytral interval 5 with two setiferous punctures. The authors suspect that the female 
<typeStatus id="CF1FCDDBE331FFDFFC10FA93964AFAD1" box="[957,1062,1378,1402]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFBE7FA939684FAD1" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[1098,1256,1378,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="townsendi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFBE7FA939684FAD1" box="[1098,1256,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. townsendi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent an aberrant form of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFE14FA739023FA32" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[441,591,1410,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviceps">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFE14FA739023FA32" box="[441,591,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. parviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a hybrid specimen between 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFC60FA73960FFA32" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[973,1123,1410,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviceps">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFC60FA73960FFA32" box="[973,1123,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. parviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE331FFDFFB0CFA739758FA32" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[1185,1332,1410,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tairuense">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE331FFDFFB0CFA739758FA32" box="[1185,1332,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">B. tairuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
